article.headline: Sterling Young scores 25 to propel Florida A&M past Trinity (FL) 130-58
article.description: — Sterling Young had 25 points in Florida A&M's 130-58 victory over Trinity (FL) on Friday night.
article.linkText: Sterling Young scores 25 to propel Florida A&M past Trinity (FL) 130-58
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- — Sterling Young had 25 points in Florida A&M's 130-58 victory over Trinity (FL) on Friday night. Young shot 7 of 9 from the field, including 6 for 7 from 3-point range, and went 5 for 5 from the line for the Rattlers (3-5). Kaleb Washington scored 22 points while going 10 of 14 (2 for 4 from 3-point range). Shaqir O'Neal shot 8 of 13 from the field and 3 for 5 from the line to finish with 20 points. Donald Nunnery finished with 18 points and seven rebounds for the Tigers. Jason McCoy added 17 points and Alexander Dawson scored nine. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
